provisions.content:
For the application of the provisions of this Law, public property shall mean the property owned or subjected partially or totally to the control and administration of the following authorities:
The Ministries and other governmental bodies;
The Public authorities and institutions;
The Private societies and institutions and cooperative societies;
The Companies if one of the ministries or any other governmental bodies or a public authority or institution holds a share therein.
Any other authority the funds thereof are considered as public funds in accordance with the law.

A punishment of imprisonment for a period not less than one year and not exceeding three years shall apply to anyone who commits any of the following acts:
1- Opens or runs a whorehouse or contributing to its opening or running;
2- Owns a house or a store and leasing it knowing that it is going to be used as a brothel;

A punishment of imprisonment for a period not less than one year and not exceeding five years shall apply to anyone who commits the following crimes:
1- Grooms a female to commit adultery;
2- Instigates, induces, seduces a female in any way to commit adultery or to frequent a brothel in order to commit debauchery whether inside or outside the country;
3- Leading, instigating or seducing a male by in any way to commit sodomy or dissipation;
4- Inducing or seducing a male or a female in any way to commit illegal or immoral actions;
5- Bringing, exposing or accepting a male or a female for the purpose of sexual exploitation.

A punishment of life imprisonment shall apply to anyone who commits theft with all of the following conditions;
at night;
if committed by at least two people;
if one of the culprits holds a seen or concealed weapon;
if committed at residential premises, or at premises intended for residential purposes or annexes thereof where entry is gained by trespass, break-in or use of duplicate keys against the will of their owner, or by wearing the uniform of a policeman or by assuming a false identity claiming it to be issued by competent authorities or by alleging to be a public officer, or colluding with one of the inhabitants or by such other illegal means.
if committed with the use of force or under the threat of using a weapon.

A punishment of imprisonment for a period not exceeding seven years shall apply to anyone who committed theft in any of the following cases:
If committed with the use of force or under the threat of using a weapon;
If the Theft is committed at night, by two persons or more, one is carrying a visible or hidden weapon;
If the Theft is committed at night, at residential premises, by one person is carrying a visible or hidden weapon;

A punishment of imprisonment for a period not exceeding five years shall apply to anyone who commits a theft in one of the following two cases:
1- If it is committed at night;
2- If it is committed by a person holding a seen or concealed weapon.

A punishment of imprisonment for a period not exceeding three years shall apply to anyone who commits a theft crime, embezzles, or purloins in any one of the following cases:
At a place intended for worship;
At residential premises, or at premises intended for residential purposes or annexes thereof;
Onboard any conveyance, at a terminal, seaport or airport;
By trespass, break-in, or with the use of original or duplicate keys against the will of their owner;
By a person who has assumed a false identity or alleged that he/she is undertaking or assigned to public service.
By two persons or more.
By transportation workers when, in the line of their duty, delivering the things being transported.
Against injured persons during wartime even if they are enemies

A punishment shall be imprisonment for a period not less than one year and not exceeding five years, and a fine not less than ten thousand riyals and not more than twenty thousand riyals shall apply to anyone who:
1- Forges a credit card;
2- Knowingly, uses a forged or stolen credit card;
3- Knowingly, accepts invalid, forged or stolen credit cards;
4- Makes, equipment or machines used in the production of credit cards without due authorization.

A punishment of imprisonment for a period not exceeding one year, and a fine not more than five thousand riyals, or any of them shall apply to anyone who:
Cuts off, uproots or scrapes off a tree belonging to a third party.
Damages crops or add toxins to plants or a sown field belonging to a third party.;
